Chinese Vice Premier Liu He, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, speaks at a teleconference on paying off arrears to private, small and medium-sized enterprises in Beijing, capital of China, Oct. 21, 2019. (Xinhua/Ding Haitao)Â Chinese Vice Premier Liu He on Monday underscored efforts to ensure the full completion of this year's task of clearing arrears. Work on clearing arrears by related departments is making smooth progress at the moment, Liu remarked at a teleconference on paying off arrears of private, small and medium-sized enterprises. Clearing arrears is a significant political task that is not only important for government credibility but is also closely related to economic growth, social expectation, employment and people's livelihood, Liu stressed. Efforts should be made to give timely response to social concerns and strengthen the follow-up assessment to guarantee full completion of this year's clearing arrears task, he added. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US PG&E blackouts reveal mismanaged concern over public safetyGirls three times more likely to be victims of cyberbullying Great Pacific Airshow